// SDLC Security Activities at Each Phase:

// 1. REQUIREMENTS
// - Define who can access what (access control requirements)
// - Define data classification (public, internal, confidential, secret)
// - Define compliance requirements (GDPR, PCI-DSS, HIPAA)

// 2. DESIGN
// - Threat modeling (STRIDE)
// - Security architecture review
// - Choose authentication/authorisation model

// 3. IMPLEMENTATION
// - Follow secure coding standards
// - Use approved libraries
// - Peer code review with security checklist

// 4. TESTING
// - Static analysis (find bugs without running code)
// - Dynamic analysis (find bugs while running)
// - Penetration testing (simulate attacks)

// 5. DEPLOYMENT
// - Harden server configuration
// - Remove default accounts
// - Enable logging and monitoring

// 6. MAINTENANCE
// - Patch vulnerabilities promptly
// - Monitor for attacks
// - Incident response plan

